Jeopardy-style CTF
Attack-Defence CTF
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Man-in-the-middle attack(MITM):
    -is a cyberattack where the attacker secretly relays and possibly alters the communications between two parties who believe that they are directly communicating with each other.
     MITM attacks usually imply an active adversary: one who will change the contents of the message before passing it on. While in sniffing an eavesdropper will be passive(that is
     they will not modify the traffic).
